,Not Recommended,249990,10571559,"Posted: 20 June, 2014",all,Phase,"20 June 2014It's with Great shame that i will advise not to bother with Forced yet.This is one of the greatest ideas and the game itself feels amazing to Play, so why the Negative?Forced is currently suffering from a Number of bad Game Design Choices and certain Bugs.Myself and a 2nd player reached the second boss with a few bugs but nothing horrible.We were pleased with the game and wanted to go further, but the the only reason we got as far as we did (level 2) is that the ease of the game covered the design flaws to that point. When the complexity (not difficulty) ramps up you begin to realise the flaws.Flaw 1: The Camera is Horrible. This game is centered around it's co-op mode and it could be fun, but the game currently runs on a single camera system that always keeps you, you parner and or the boss in it's view. This is fine until the level complexity increases at which point characters can become very hard to see and the camera distances itself massivly. A bug also occurs here where you can actually walk your character off camera, and if your team members are fighting or solving in opposite corners you can't see youself at all, causing all sorts of issues. Local Camera is heavily needed, keep the player and the Boss (for example) and fix the edge Clipping, letting your party do as they please, Colored Player indicators are amazing in that situation to determine where people are, or even a very simple minimap if its THAT complicated.Flaw 2: That leads me nicely onto this. The company have decided to op out of being able to walk through your enemys. This feels good until you encounter more then 2-3 at once, at which Point they surround you, locking you in place as you can't Push them. There are knockback mechanics and escape mechanics you can choose for your character. But now you find yourself in a position where fun or damage talents are unusable because you need movement survival and escape for when you get Trapped or Knocked back. This ALSO has a bug of its own, where EVERY ability that can be classed as an escape or survival can just ranomdly not work (Non more evident than using the shield weapons 'dash' ability, where it often takes you no-where, despite showing the animations of you moving, or even teleports you back to where you started)Flaw 3: The gameplay lends itself to heavy hack and slash combat that's real fun. But more enemys means you quickly start to realise an issue. You can't Heal. 2/4 classes have heals, one is decent but on a LONG Cooldown (And interuptable via knockback), and the other is a heal over time effect with a speed boost, that whilst being mandetory is only useful for the speed, and requires spamming. The only other way to heal is the Poles you can drift the Orb over, which also require spamming in order to stand a chance. What this leads to is a Cluster F*** of enemys who synergise very badly and do nothing but follow you in a Lump. You find yourself unable to find many safe attack areas and spend the majority of combat running around avoiding the fight because you can't heal, or because the enemys invincible until the boss gives you a charge to defeat him (a charge you can only call to you, and that almost Kills you if it detonates nearby).All in all, this game has the potential to be one of the best co-ops out there, These issues however make it frustrating and awkward to play. After a lot of frustrating game mechanics issues, we left Forced behind at level 2. No amount of skill or learning will get you past RNG when your dash's, escapes and heals don't work. No amount of skill or enjoment will get you past camera fails, where you cannot see your Chatacer.Current? 3/10These simple issues Fixed? 7-8/10 EASILY."
