76561198044989881,Recommended,249990,13696571,"Posted: 29 December, 2014",all,Santoshka,"Forced is one of those games to make you rage uncontrollably. Its difficult, sometimes obtuse, and requires impeccable communication. And its damn fun. This isn't a game you can autopilot through. You have to be on your A game 100% of the time, which for me meant taking a break every couple of levels. However the completion of a challenge is extremely rewarding.Unlike many hack and slashers, this game does not focus on equipment or leveling skills, instead it provides skills that have distinct tradeoffs against other skills and may need to be optimized between levels. Your characters never get more health or do more damage, but they do get skills that combo together to do more damage.Art style was basic but competent, character readability was very good. Sound was basic but competent.I got this game as early access and was impressed by the improvement and overall progress that the devs accomplished. The game has online coop and local coop with up to 4 players. While you can play by yourself, its singnificantly more fun with friends."
