,Recommended,249990,9760770,"Posted: 8 April, 2014",all,Pretend Penguin,"A fantastic couch co-op game! Not enough games have this feature anymore but nothing beats getting some friends around, hooking up 4 controllers and having a laugh.The game looks beautiful, especially as you get through the game and explore different scenery.You play through ""trials"" which are small levels which feature puzzles, combat and strategy. By completing these you earn crystals which you use to unlock skills with your character class which you can change at any time.  Each trial has 3 crystals to obtain, one for completing the level, one for completing a said challenge within the trial and one for compelting the trial within a time limit. Some of the challanges are impossible to get at a lower level which means you need revisit levels you have done before to increase your crystal total.A fun game with depth that I did not expect. I expected this to be twin stick shooter but turned out to be so much more!8.5/10"
,Recommended,249990,8179854,"Posted: 21 December, 2013",all,[UCF] Enduro,"So bought this game as a 4 pack with some friends. Totally worth it! It's a sorta hack/slash rpg'ish puzzle game. You control 1 of 4 different characters (hammer, bow, shield, daggers) each has their own set of skills, passives, and playstyles. You work with your friends to navigate innovative maps and figure out puzzles all with the help of a little orb spirt guy. Every person can call this orb to their position so it can be trolly if everyone is spamming. It requires a great deal of communication as it sometimes requires you to bounce the orb from person to person but without letting it hit objects (part of the puzzle). I highly recommend you pick this up in a 4 pack and play with friends over voice chat as it can be very fun, quirky, rewarding, and frustrating all in one but there is sense of accomplishment similar to when you first beat a boss in an MMO when you nail a puzzle while 3 of your friends are dead and you are teetering on life. The simple combat systems works perfectly as there is plenty of other object happening on the screen to keep you active and always thinking.There isn't a game out there like this on the market that I am aware. Anyone who plays with friends should pick this up."
