,Not Recommended,249990,18567791,"Posted: 19 October, 2015",all,Aequitarian,"Bought it on sale for $2. Its an alright puzzle game, but nothing particularly compelling. Definitely not worth the $14.99 sticker price.Pros: Different weapon sets are useful for different levels, decent co-op play. Low cost on sale.Bosses you beat become toned down normal enemies in following levels, which introduces some neat mechanics in mundane combat.cons: Almost no replayability. Progression requires you to beat levels under a timer and while adhering to generally more difficult challenges, so look forward to playing all of them several times as you go through the story.Low variety of enemies. You'll see the same ones every single level.Puzzles are highly simplistic. Out of 20 story levels only a handful aren't painfully obvious. About half of challenges are super easy to get and you'll end up reaching them just by playing the level, the rest are frustrating and include a strong element of luck requiring you to replay the level multiple times.Stunlock for days. Not all classes have invincibility frames, and several enemy types can pin you against the wall or dogpile you and stunlock you to death. The completely invisible enemies that attack from invis without breaking it only add to this, as they make some attacks legitimately unavoidable.Camera is terribad. It has a maximum zoom and a fixed angle, combined with all the knockbacks its not unsual to have people stuck offscreen.Almost no multiplayer scene: less than five games at a time, coming off of an 85% off sale. Unless you've got friends who own it or buy a fourpack look forward to going it alone."
