76561197963107234,Recommended,249990,9715591,"Posted: 3 April, 2014",all,Trig,"Forced, overall, is a great game, but it has plenty of bugs which can cause major issues when playing with friends.I bought the four pack, and have had tons of fun with my friends in this game, but I've also suffered through a couple of hours trying to deal with bugs just to be able to play.Pros:The spirit mentor mechanic is extremely unique and makes this game a ton of fun. It is challenging because everyone can control it equally, and often all players need to work together and coordinate positioning and timing to complete levels.The levels themselves are challenging, but easily doable with a little effort. The challenge gems on the levels, which unlock extra abilities for all players, are quite difficult at times and give the game a much harder goal for those who want it.Each level is unique and fresh, and the game continues to throw new content at the players from start to finish. This makes for an extremely fun game that is made even better when playing with friends.Cons:For no apparent reason, some people are unable to join certain game lobbies to play with friends. The only solution I've found to this is to continually remake and have different parties host until it happens to work. This usually takes 5-10 minutes of remaking games for everyone to be able to play together.Once a level is loaded, there's a chance some players will be unable to move. Sometimes this is fixed by simply restarting the level which takes only a few seconds, but sometimes this bug just won't go away until the entire game is remade, which can make the process take several minutes, especially if there's a connection bug.For an unknown reason, some players will not be rewarded gems for completeing the level in game. Because the game will not let anyone progress until all members have equipped all their abilities, this can cause major problems early in the game. Fortunately, all gems are rewarded upon making a new game. Once again, this is easily done if everyone can connect to the lobby without any issues, but if you run into the connection bug I mentioned, it can delay your gaming experience even more.The first two hours I spent in this game, I probably got to play for half an hour. Now that workarounds to most of the bugs have been figured out by my friends and I, it's not so bad. The bugs are annoying, but easily fixed if you have the time to spare. For most games, these bugs would be a deal breaker for me, but because the gameplay itself is so enjoyable and unique, I don't mind. I highly recommend this game, but be aware of the issues it has before going into it."
