76561197973774604,Not Recommended,249990,14016644,"Posted: 16 January, 2015",all,The Angry Gnome,"After spending a few hours with this game, I can only conclude that the title appears to be a reference to the in-game dialogue. Videogames are notorious for poor writing and even worse voice acting but it's been a while since I've come across one as incessantly annoying as FORCED.What about the gameplay? It's not bad... more or less a Gauntlet clone with light RPG elements and a few interesting puzzles. The levels are mostly bland and forgettable. Often they will include interactive elements that are neither self-evident nor properly explained by the game's everpresent, never useful narrator. (Think Navi from Ocarina with no grasp of the English language.)Considering I bought it for a dollar, I wouldn't exactly call this game a waste of money. I'm sure glad I didn't spend any more than that on it though. For a much more robust top-down ARPG experience, try Magicka or Gauntlet."
