76561198072237275,Recommended,249990,34245635,Posted: 14 August,all,FreeRunnerBu,"FORCED can really call itself a coop-game!Basicly the story is about four gladiators who have to survive various arenas and bosses, literally they are forced to do so. Balfus, an orb, is the only one helping them. Also, he is the key to solve many problems while fighting and clearing objectives.Refering to the first sentence, I want to point out why I personally think so. There are three major things to mention. Communication, timing and tactics! This is what you need to successfully play this game.Grab your friends and play!"
,Recommended,249990,34639386,Posted: 31 August,all,DJHarmony,"This is one of those games that I knew going in would be challenging, and I'll say, it's that good kind of challenging. The game seems like it's out to kill you and belittle you, but in a way that makes sense and adds to the fullfilment of doing well. The controls are pretty darn easy to get the hang of and while the enemies can sometimes be a bit overwhelming you will find that there are easy ways to deal with all of them as time goes on. The story isn't exactly the most original in terms of these Guantlet style games, but it doesn't need to be. The bosses you face all feel legitimately threatening and your guide is probably one of the most useful in gaming history, used to solve puzzles and activate certain power-ups/healing fountains. The feeling of being the underdog who surpasses all trials is a feeling that every gamer should get to feel."
